  "prompt": "What are the best small classes for freshmen at Western Carolina University?",
  "response": "At Western Carolina University, the best small classes for freshmen can vary depending on the specific interests and majors of students. However, some general recommendations for small class experiences might include:\n\n1. **First-Year Seminars**: These are often designed to help transition students into university life and can cover various topics. They typically involve smaller class sizes and focus on critical thinking and academic skills.\n\n2. **Introductory courses in specialized fields**: Look for introductory classes in your chosen major that are capped at a lower enrollment. For example, sections of courses in the humanities or social sciences may offer more personalized attention.\n\n3. **Language and Literature Classes**: Beginning language classes or literature courses often have smaller enrollments, allowing for more interaction.\n\n4. **Creative Arts Classes**: Courses in art, music, or theater can also have smaller class sizes and provide a hands-on learning experience.\n\n5. **Electives**: Consider choosing unique elective courses that interest you. These classes might have fewer students and provide opportunities to engage closely with the material and the instructor.\n\nTo find the most current offerings and details about class sizes for specific departments, it\u2019s best to check the Western Carolina University course catalog or consult with an academic advisor. They can help identify small class options that align with your interests and academic goals.",
